edu.umaryland.igs.idea
Class LikelihoodData

java.lang.Object
  edu.umaryland.igs.idea.LikelihoodData
All Implemented Interfaces:
CustomRenderable
public class LikelihoodData
extends Object
implements CustomRenderable

The class LikelihoodData encapsulates the results of a likelihood ratio test and the data used to arrive at those results. A LikelihoodData object may also represent the likelihood score of a model which did not serve as an alternative model in an LRT, in which case the tested field should be false.

LikelihoodData

public LikelihoodData(double amls,
                      double nmls,
                      double ts,
                      double pv,
                      boolean s,
                      SiteSubstitutionModel am,
                      SiteSubstitutionModel nm)
This constructs a full-fledged LikelihoodData object representing an actual LRT. The tested field is automatically set to true since this is implied when the seven-arg constructor is called.

Parameters:
amls - the likelihood score on which these LRT results are based
nmls - the score of the null model compared to the alternative model in the LRT
ts - the test statistic compared to chi^2 in the LRT
pv - the P-value of the test-statistic
s - whether the P-value is significant at 5%
am - the alternative model in the LRT
nm - the null model in the LRT

Method Detail

likelihoodScore

public double likelihoodScore()
The likelihoodScore method returns the likelihood score of the alternative model in the LRT or, in the case of a degenerate LikelihoodData object, the likelihood score the object represents.

Returns:
the alternative model's lnL or the lnL of a model which did not serve as an alternative model

toString

public String toString()
The toString method of a customRenderable class should return a string representation of an object suitable for printing in a table cell. LikelihoodData's implementation simply returns the lnL score of the alternative model (or the lnL score represented by a degenerate LikelihoodData object) as a String.

Overrides:
toString in class Object
Returns:
the alternative model's lnL (or the lnL represented by a degenerate object) as a String

customRendering

public Component customRendering()
LikelihoodData's implementation of customRendering returns a a label with a check or X icon. Mousing over this icon activates a tool tip containing the HTML document returned by details.
